               <head>William Heytesbury, <title>Sophismata</title></head>
               <physDesc>
                  <p><note>Comprising three originally separate MSS</note></p>
                  <p><secFol><damage><gap unit="char" quantity="2"/></damage> est causa</secFol></p>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support><p>Comprising three originally separate MSS, the first on mixed
                              vellum and paper, the last two single quires on vellum (HSOS/<term
                                 type="disposition">HFFH</term>). In manuscript 1, scribes 1 and 2
                              simply alternate vellum and paper leaves (the vellum always outside);
                              scribe 3 uses a vellum sheet to form outer and central bifolia and
                              regularly has two groups of two paper sheets each between these and a
                              third vellum bifolium. The paper leaves do not appear to be formed by
                              folding but from cutting appropriately sized bifolia from sheets; wire
                              lines run both vertically and horizontally, and watermarks appear
                              irregularly and indiscriminately. The first twelve quires are on very
                              archaic paper, with pronounced widely spaced wire lines. There are
                              four stocks:</p>
                           <p><hi rend="italic">A</hi>: <watermark><term type="watermarkMotif"
                                    >Monts/Dreiberg</term></watermark> in quire 3;</p>
                           <p><hi rend="italic">B</hi>, <hi rend="italic">C</hi>: <watermark><term
                                    type="watermarkMotif">Ciseaux of two types,</term></watermark>
                              one each in quires 4 and 5;</p>
                           <p><hi rend="italic">D</hi>: <watermark><term type="watermarkMotif"
                                    >Horn</term></watermark> in quire 8;</p>
                           <p><hi rend="italic">E</hi>: <watermark><term type="watermarkMotif"
                                    >Fleur, perhaps more than one type</term></watermark>, in quires
                              16–18.</p></support>
                        <extent>Fols. 1 + <measure type="leaf" quantity="193">193</measure>
                           (numbered fols. 1–194; fol. 150 is assigned to a tab sewn to fol. 151) +
                           i (numbered fol. ii). <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height quantity="160">160</height>
                              <width min="115" max="120">115</width>
                           </dimensions><note>(after fol. 116, slightly wider, about 120
                           mm)</note></extent>
                        <foliation>An original foliation beginning at fol. 2 and running to fol. 119
                           (numbered 120).</foliation>
                        <condition><locus from="2" to="2">Fol. 2</locus> lower margin patched with a
                           small bit of Latin MS on vellum, and a further vellum slip set into the
                           paper at the foot of <locus from="7" to="7">fol. 7</locus>.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>Various page formats noted below.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1750" notAfter="1950">
