                  <provenance>Ker could read under ultraviolet light what we can no longer clearly
                     discern, the erased inscriptions, ‘quaternus fratris <persName
                        key="person_4698" role="sgn">Iohannis de Claxton</persName> ordinis
                     predicatorum Bostonie’ (<locus from="181r" to="181r">fol. 181</locus>, upper
                     margin) and the words ‘quod <note type="editorial">[? quaternus]</note> frater
                     I Claxton de Booston’ (<locus from="188v" to="188v">fol. 188<hi
                           rend="superscript">v</hi></locus>, below the inscription described next);
                     for the ascription of <locus from="181" to="188">fols. 181–8</locus> alone to
                     the <orgName key="org_278" role="fmo" cert="medium">Boston Dominicans</orgName>, see
                           <bibl><title>MLGB</title> 11, 231</bibl>.</provenance>
                  <provenance>‘Ista sunt sophismata Fratris <persName key="person_4699" role="fmo"
                        >Willielmi Louent</persName>
                     <note type="editorial">[the name over an erasure]</note> ordinis predicatorum
                     cicestrie <note type="editorial">[again over an erasure]</note>’ (the upper
                     margin, <locus from="188v" to="188v">fol. 188<hi rend="superscript"
                        >v</hi></locus>) (<orgName key="org_277" role="fmo">the Chichester
                        Dominican convent</orgName>, <bibl>Ker <title>MLGB</title> 51,
                     248)</bibl>.</provenance>
                  <provenance notBefore="1475" notAfter="1500">Ker also read with ultraviolet
                     another erased inscription (s. xv ex., <locus from="180v" to="180v">fol. 180<hi
                           rend="superscript">v</hi></locus>, below an earlier contents table added
                     s. xv) ‘Iste quaternus <damage> </damage>
                     <orgName key="org_187" role="fmo">ordinis predicatorum leycestrie</orgName>’
                           (<bibl><title>MLGB</title> 113</bibl>, fols. 1–180 only).</provenance>
                  <provenance notBefore="1500" notAfter="1600">Pen-trials <persName
                        key="person_4700" role="sgn">‘Mary Whyght’</persName> twice (<locus
                        from="173v" to="173v">fol. 173<hi rend="superscript">v</hi></locus>, s.
                     xvi).</provenance>
                  <provenance>The old shelfmark ‘Abac: ij N. 51.’ (<locus from="1r" to="1r">fol.
                        1</locus>, margin).</provenance>
